                " \nMINTEK\n ",
                " \n \nCHIEF OPERATOR: FACILITIES AND OPERATIONS\nListing reference: minte_000152\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 3 November 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Scientific, Research & Development\nJob category: RandD, Science and Scientific Research\nLocation: Randburg\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: Yes\n \nIntroduction\nMintek has an exciting career opportunity for a chief operator who will be responsible for logistics and operational issues involved in materials handling, commissioning, maintenance, and operation of laboratory and pilot scale furnace facilities in the Pyrometallurgy Division. High level of diligence is expected to ensure high level of productivity, output and cost management.\n \nJob description\nResponsible for logistics and operational issues, including the commissioning, maintenance, and operation of laboratory and pilot scale furnace facilities, in the Pyrometallurgy Division.\nAssisting in handling and processing of solid and molten materials in a safe and responsible manner.\nPrepare equipment and facilities for use and check the operability of standard equipment and facilities to ensure that they are ready for use, and must provide technical and procedural advice to staff on how to operate equipment, which equipment settings are the optimal, etc.\nGeneral management and coordination of bulk sample storage areas (e.g. steel shed, bushed and other storage areas)\nCoordinating bulk deliveries, dispatch, and storage of bulk materials, including keeping updated inventories to allow effective retrieval.\nCoordinating housekeeping and maintaining bulk storage areas and materials to ensure materials are stored properly to avoid contamination and/or degradation.\nUndertaking preparation of bulk samples such as screening, blending, mixing, and drying as well as re-bagging\nAssisting in refractory lining of pilot furnaces and other general pilot facility preparation activities\nCoordinating the collection and delivery of required raw materials from storage to pilot bays for campaigns or test work, including coordinating the handling and tipping of products from ladles, separation of products, crushing to smaller lumps, bagging, weighing, and labelling during pilot campaigns.\nContributing to continuous improvement efforts on infrastructure through standardization of procedures while delivering on performance against agreed metrics. This includes conducting detailed investigations into facility bottlenecks, understanding root causes, and establishing control measures to prevent reoccurrence.\nProviding technical support to internal and external clients to ascertain scope requirements and to timeously deliver on research and commercial projects, including supervision and training of O- and P-level operators, interns and contractors involved.\nEvaluating facilities, processes, systems, products, or new developments to identify opportunities and deficiencies to ensure continuous improvement.\nConform to all relevant SHEQ procedures, guidelines, and rules, and ensure that relevant risks and hazards are identified and managed through Mintek-approved risk assessments and procedures. This includes ensuring that all relevant SOPs are up to date and complied with.\n \nMinimum requirements\nBEHAVIOURAL COMPETENCIES:\nTeam player who enjoys working on a variety of tasks.\nExcellent interpersonal skills\nSelf-driven\nAbility to work in a stressful and demanding environment\nAbility to manage shifts and work in hot and dusty plant environments \n \nJOB KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERIENCE:\n10 years\u2019 experience in the operation of relevant pyrometallurgical unit processes and/or equipment.\nKnowledge or experience with SHEQ systems is non-negotiable.\nA strong understanding of electric arc furnaces and raw materials handling is highly advantageous.\nPhysically fit\n \nQUALIFICATIONS:\nGrade 12\nTrade certificate in a relevant field is an added advantage\n \nAPPLY\n \n \n \n ",
                "HEAD: RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT - MAC\nListing reference: minte_000153\nListing status: Online\nApply by: 2 November 2023\n \nPosition summary\nIndustry: Scientific, Research & Development\nJob category: Other: Mining\nLocation: Randburg\nContract: Permanent\nRemuneration: Market Related\nEE position: Yes\n \nIntroduction\nMintek has an exciting opportunity for an individual that will manage the three technical teams responsible for RDI in the Measurement and Control Division, namely, the Process Control team, 4IR team and Instruments team. The focus areas of the division\u2019s RDI activities are measurement, actuation, control and optimization of minerals processing plants. Provide technical expertise and guidance to the teams in areas of speciality and keep up-to-date with all technologies and business in the Group\u2019s work. Ascertain needs and trends in the industry, develop, and execute appropriate research programmes to ensure long-term sustainability of the division by ensuring innovative and relevant R&D is undertaken aimed at producing new technologies in line with the division\u2019s long-term plans and strengthening and expanding the technical abilities of the Group.\n \nJob description\nKEY PERFORMANCE INDICATORS:\nLeadership\nLive the Mintek values, foster a culture of collaboration within Mintek.\nProvide scientific leadership in specific discipline.\nCreate an environment for the group to succeed and manage outputs.7\nMaintain consistently visible leadership.\nStrategy\nDrive the Division\u2019s RDI strategy and operations, and develop plans for the implementation of the strategy.\nSupport the Division\u2019s business development and commercialization leg and manage the execution of strategic programmes.\nVisibility and credibility \u2013 ensuring that publication outputs, including journal and conference papers, are met.\nProvide technical direction and mentoring to staff in the Group\nMonitoring and Evaluation of project milestones to motivate for further funding\nFinancial Sustainability:\nSecure the Group\u2019s Budget.\nBalance the RDI portfolio funding and targets as agreed.\nEnsure that there are effective inter Discipline collaborations and collaborations between Clusters to ensure that targets are met.\nPrepares large funding proposals to attract funding from a variety of sources to support the activities of the Group\nPeople and Planning\nEnsure that the core Group\u2019s plans are aligned with Mintek\u2019s strategy and the needs of the Division\u2019s market.\nEnsure that adequate Divisional planning is done to ensure effective delivery of the plans.\nEnsure that the Group is adequately resourced, with a particular focus on SET staff and resources. Also ensuring succession planning.\nDrive the transformation agenda in the Group.\nContribute to the refinement and development of the Divisional strategy and plans.\nPerformance Management\nDeliver on the Group\u2018s KPIs.\nUndertake performance management for the Group.\nEnsure that systems and tools are in place to monitor and measure the delivery of RDI activities.\nRelationship management and reporting\nStakeholder engagement, including the development of relationships with new stakeholders, stakeholder management and satisfaction for both internal and external stakeholders.\nReporting on all RDI activities of the Group.\nLead Co-development and Co-funding initiatives.\n \nMinimum requirements\nBEHAVIORAL COMPETENCIES\nBe able to work in a team\nExcellent communication and organisational skills\nAttention to detail, ability to follow up and take initiative\n \nQUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE\nMasters degree in Chemical/Electrical/Electronics Engineering/Computer Science/Physics or relevant\nIdeal: PhD\n8 - 10 years\u2019 experience on the relevant field\nSupervisory experience\n \nAPPLY"
