                " \nTRANSNET\n ",
                " \n \nThis advert is open for application by external applicants.\n \nEquity Statement : Preference will be given to suitably qualified Applicants who are members of the designated groups in line with the Employment Equity Plan and Targets of the Organisation/Operating Division.\n \nApplicants that are interested in applying for any of the advertised positions must apply by registering on the Careers section of the Transnet Internet. Please take care in completing all required details on the profile, and then apply for the position.\n \nAlternative Application Methods: (Completed Curriculum Vitae to be submitted)\nPost :\nE-mail :\nFax :\n \nThe closing date is on 01.11.2023. \nIt is the responsibility of the applicant to ensure that HR has received the application before the closing date of the advertisement.\n \nNote: if you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of this advertisement please consider your application as unsuccessful.\nAny questions regarding the application or recruitment process should be sent in writing to\nDIPUO.MNIKATI@TRANSNET.NET. \nWe urge all our employees, clients, members of the public and our suppliers to report any kind of fraud or corruption at Transnet. Call the hotline toll free number: 0800 003 056 or email Transnet@tip-offs.com\n \nOperating Division : Transnet Corporate Centre\nPosition Title : (Readvert) Spec. Training: Marine Engineering\nEmployee Group : Permanent\nDepartment : Fac.Tml&Marine\nLocation : Bayhead\nReporting To : Snr Spec : Marine Operations Training\nGrade Level : E\nReference Number : 6014639\n \nPosition Purpose:\n\u2022Ensure effective management and delivery of core marine engineering training for port operations, seagoing interventions, as well as safety related and safety critical training in line with customer needs and requirements in order to fulfil the national mandate of the business targeting internal, external and cross-border clients\n\u2022 Manage and ensure ongoing compliance with relevant statutory, regulatory and Quality Assurance standards and requirements i.e., Academy governance, TIMS, SAMSA, QCTO, TETA etc\n\u2022 Keep abreast with leading practice and latest trends to ensure continuous technological advancement and adoption of training delivery best practice\n\u2022 Manage training-related projects and assets, facilities and equipment ensuring proper maintenance and asset lifecycle management to support the delivery of learning within the Faculty\n \nPosition outputs:\nTraining Delivery\n\u2022 Manage the delivery of marine engineering seagoing and port operations training and all safety-related training to both internal and external clients to enable skilled and competent employees that will contribute to safe and productive business operations\n\u2022Execute the Faculty of Port Terminals and Marine annual training business plan and subsequently manage and control the specific plans relevant to business operations to meet objectives and targets\n\u2022Support revenue generating initiatives by marketing training solutions to the Transnet National Ports Authority, local and cross border industry whenever possible\n\u2022Manage and monitor projects on an \u2018as and when\u2019 basis ensuring that they are executed within budget, at the right quality as per scope of work, and within the agreed timelines\n\u2022Manage Marine engineering training interventions according to the approved Workplace Skills Plan (WSP) and attend to ad-hoc requests\n\u2022Align, implement and interface training process (e.g. Training delivery, On-the-Job Training (OJT), Assessment, Moderation) to maintain a safe working environment and to enable compliance with the SAMSA and any other legislative requirements\n\u2022Manage the interface of the learner training data with the Shared Services Centre through the learning administration standard operating procedures\n\u2022Set, plan and manage the implementation of marine training delivery objectives with respect to time, quality and cost constraints; identify, track and mitigate risks; monitor and close audit findings to sustain continuous improvement\n\u2022Conduct training locally and cross-border\nStakeholder Relations Management\n\u2022Build sound relationships with internal and external stakeholders in line with Transnet policies and procedures\n\u2022Interact and engage with People Management TNPA regarding operational training requirements\nGovernance & Compliance\n\u2022 Ensure compliance to relevant legislation, regulations, policies and processes to sustain the accreditations from professional and quality assurance bodies (SAMSA, QCTO, TETA), skills development Legislation and practices, namely NQF, SANS, SAQA, ECSA etc.\n\u2022 Manage the alignment and implementation of training delivery processes and procedures in accordance with the Transnet\nIntegrated Management System (TIMS)\n\u2022Manage the implementation of the Board of Inquiries (BOI) recommendations and serve as a subject matter expert for BOI and First Line investigations of incidents\nPeople Management\n\u2022Manage, coach and develop staff as required\n\u2022Manage staff to ensure that maximum levels of competency, efficiency and safety is achieved and maintained through the implementation of Education, Training and Development (ETD) practices, Employees Relations (ER), Performance Management and Talent Management within the Department\nFinancial management\n\u2022Manage training budgets and contracts in line with the Budget Guidelines, Procurement Procedures Manual (PPM), Public Finance Management Act (PFMA) and Contract Management Policy and report deviations\n \nQualifications & Experience:\n\u2022 ND Marine/Mechanical/Electrical Engineering (NQF6), Advanced Diploma (NQF level 7) in related Engineering studies with a minimum of 8 years\u2019 experience as Marine Engineer of which at least 2-3 years at a supervisory level as a Marine operations manager/Marine technical manager/Fleet manager/Chief marine engineer officer Feeder pool:\n\u2022MS3 - Chief Marine Engineering Officer 3\n\u2022MM2 - Chief Marine Engineer Officer > 3000KW / Marine Technical Manager Engine MTM/Fleet Manager experience 5 \u2013 6 yrs\n\u2022SAMSA Level 1 or 2 STCW Certificate of Competence and Chief Engineer Port Operations CoC\n\u2022Must obtain OD ETDP qualification within 24 months\n\u2022Post graduate degree will be an advantage\n\u2022Project Management qualification will be an advantage\n \nStandard Job Requirements\n\u2022 Driver\u2019s licence code 08\n\u2022 Must be willing to obtain a valid South African Passport or be in possession of such a passport\n\u2022 Must be willing to travel as required and approved by the business\n\u2022 Requirement of trust and honesty in the handling of finances as per the National Credit Act Amendment 19\n \nCompetencies:\n\u2022Strategy & Sustainability\n\u2022Inspirational Leadership\n\u2022Business Performance and Delivery\n\u2022Relationship Management\n\u2022Corporate Governance & Compliance\n\u2022Personal Mastery\n \n\nPLEASE NOTE: Transnet, its employees or representatives never ask for a fee from job seekers. Any such requests are fraudulent. Please report any suspicious activities in this regard to the Transnet anti-fraud line on 0800 003 056.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nThis advert is open for application by external applicants.\n \nEquity Statement :Preference will be given to suitably qualified Applicants who are members of the designated groups in line with the Employment Equity Plan and Targets of the Organisation/Operating Division.\n \nApplicants that are interested in applying for any of the advertised positions must apply by registering on the Careers section of the Transnet Internet. Please take care in completing all required details on the profile, and then apply for the position.\n \nAlternative Application Methods: (Completed Curriculum Vitae to be submitted)\nPost :\nE-mail :\nFax :\n \nThe closing date is on 01.11.2023. \nIt is the responsibility of the applicant to ensure that HR has received the application before the closing date of the advertisement.\n \nNote: if you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of this advertisement please consider your application as unsuccessful.\nAny questions regarding the application or recruitment process should be sent in writing to ZIKHONA.NCAPHA@TRANSNET.NET.\nWe urge all our employees, clients, members of the public and our suppliers to report any kind of fraud or corruption at Transnet. Call the hotline toll free number: 0800 003 056 or email Transnet@tip-offs.com\n \nOperating Division : Transnet NPA\nPosition Title : Property Officer\nEmployee Group : Permanent\nDepartment : Property Mngt\nLocation : Mossel Bay\nReporting To : Manager-Property Services\nGrade Level : H1X\nReference Number : 10298053\n \nPosition Purpose:\nEnsure effective administration of all aspects in Property Management functions by obtaining relevant approvals, prepare, process and directing of information to relevant parties which ensure correct procedures maintained, required approval obtained, correction and timeous fees and rentals charged and complete records for audit trail and research purpose.\n \nPosition outputs:\n1. Obtain valuation from Valuers for periodic review of rentals as per lease agreement, calculate new rental, and prepare agreements and record revised rental to ensure maximum income for NPA.\n2. Issuing and capturing of source documents onto the Real Estate Invoicing System for services rendered to ensure that all costs are recovered correctly and timeously and raising of debits/credits for new leases, arrear rentals, credit rentals, increases in rental, decreases in rental, deposit recovery and deposit top ups.\n3. Perform daily monitoring of correspondence to ensure timeous responses and actions taken where appropriate.\n4. Obtain approval of lease plans, dispatching of plans including recovery of charges for verge deposits, inspection fees, plan scrutiny fees, etc. to ensure that no construction work or alternation to assets are done without TNPA approved pans.\n\n5. Control and maintenance of records, i.e lists of leases, agreement files, rates files, and rent review list, list of tenants contact details etc. To ensure efficient administration functioning of department and the effective filling of all relevant correspondence for future reference, arbitration, etc.\n6. Perform functions of the secretary of the port LSEC (Lease Specification & Evaluation Committee)\n7. Obtain information and compile submission documents in line with the LSEC and NPC (National Property Committee) standards from Property Manager who negotiates a new lease and prepare the lease agreements.\n8. Compiling of various agreements with Annexure\u2019s\n9. Obtain agreement plans from Drawing Office and calculate rental\n10. Capturing sources documents and services entries on SAP.\n11. Updating of valuation database\n12. Control the BBBEE certificate status of tenants and ensure that BBBEE certificates are annually updated.\n13. Prepare and arrange for tenders to be advertised in the media\n14. Assist with the tenders process including the evaluation\n15. Assist with facilities management and relevant correspondence\n16. Assist with contract management\n \nQualifications & Experience:\n\u2022 Matric\n\u2022 Certificate in Property Management\n\u2022 Computer Packages i.e Rave, SAP, Microsoft Office\n\u2022 1-3 years\u2019 experience\n\u2022 Registered with SAOPA (South African Property Owner Association) will be an added advantage\n \nCompetencies:\n\u2022 Computer literature, (Microsoft Office)\n\u2022 Good communication Skills\n\u2022 Organising skills\n\u2022 A team worker\n\u2022 Problem solving\n\u2022 Data Accuracy\n\u2022 Desire to improve\n\u2022 Reliable\n\u2022 Client orientated\n\u2022 Independent\nSkills Required:\n\u2022 Planning\n\u2022 Leading\n\u2022 Controlling\n\u2022 Strong interpersonal skills\n\u2022 Administration skills\n\u2022 Code 08 licence\n\u2022 Telephone etiquette\n \n\nPLEASE NOTE: Transnet, its employees or representatives never ask for a fee from job seekers. Any such requests are fraudulent. Please report any suspicious activities in this regard to the Transnet anti-fraud line on 0800 003 056.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
                "This advert is open for application by external applicants.\n \nEquity Statement : Preference will be given to suitably qualified female and Persons with disabilities Applicants who are members of the designated groups in line with the Employment Equity Plan and Targets of the Organisation/Operating Division.\n \nApplicants that are interested in applying for any of the advertised positions must apply by registering on the Careers section of the Transnet Internet. Please take care in completing all required details on the profile, and then apply for the position.\n \nAlternative Application Methods: (Completed Curriculum Vitae to be submitted)\nPost :\nE-mail :\nFax :\n \nThe closing date is on 01.11.2023. \nIt is the responsibility of the applicant to ensure that HR has received the application before the closing date of the advertisement.\nNote: if you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of this advertisement please consider your application as unsuccessful.\nAny questions regarding the application or recruitment process should be sent in writing to NJABULO.MADWE@TRANSNET.NET.\nWe urge all our employees, clients, members of the public and our suppliers to report any kind of fraud or corruption at Transnet. Call the hotline toll free number: 0800 003 056 or email Transnet@tip-offs.com\n \nOperating Division : TPT POD Corporate H/O\nPosition Title : Young Professional-in-Training\nEmployee Group : Trainee\nDepartment : People Mgmt\nLocation : Durban\nReporting To : Capacity Building Manager\nGrade Level : GRAD_7\nReference Number : 203478\n \nPosition Purpose:\nProgramme is to develop a pipeline for key roles within various departments within Transnet Port Terminals (TPT) :\n\u2022 People Management - Payroll\n\u2022 ICT- (Digital Solutions Centre, web Methods, Digital Solutions Centre, Enterprise Architecture, Digital Solutions Centre\n\u2022 Legal Risk & Compliance (Safety and Environment, ERM)\n\u2022 Corporate Services\n(Business Planning & Performance Monitoring)\n\u2022 Corporate Affairs\n\u2022 Corporate Services- Strategy\n\u2022 Finance: Financial Accounting\n\u2022 Finance: Fixed Assets\n\u2022 Supply Chain Management\n \nThe Young Professional in Training is a structured 24-month training programme. The programme seeks to place Young Professional in specific areas within TPT according to their academic background, career aspirations and business requirements\n \nPosition outputs:\n\u2022 Follow a structure training programme\n\u2022 Undergo performance reviews and assessments every 6 (six) months\n\u2022 Submit monthly reports\n\u2022 Perform all duties as contained in his/her development programme, as well as which he/she may reasonably be required to perform by Transnet Port Terminals\n \nQualifications & Experience:\n\u2022 BSc-Information Technology/ Computer Science\n\u2022 Bcom-Business Information Systems\n\u2022 BSc-Hnrs/ MSc - Computers Science/ IT, AI/ML Research\n\u2022 Degree Risk/Project Risk Management\n\u2022 Degree in Safety Management or Environmental Management or Quality Management\n\u2022 Degree Risk/Project Risk Management\n\u2022 Degree in Safety Management or Environmental Management or Quality Management\n\u2022 BCom / Bachelor of Business Science, BSc (Mathematics, Statistics or Economic/ Economometrics)\n\u2022 IT systems developer or 2. IT Systems designer qualification.\n\u2022 Any Commercial Qualification with Economics , Finance, Accounting, Economic Research, Strategy or project management\n\u2022 Btech/HR Diploma\n\u2022 Bcom Accounting (NQF7)\n\u2022 B-degree SCM/Logistics, Industrial Engineering, Statistics\n \nCompetencies:\n\u2022 Must have above average computer skills\n\u2022 Ability to communicate effectively, both verbally and written\n\u2022 Must have good administration and organisation skills and the ability to handle multiple tasks\n\u2022 Ability to conduct research\n\u2022 Ability to perform within an integrated team environment\n\u2022 Good interpersonal skills\n\u2022 Professional attitude and a willingness to learn\n\u2022 Good time management\n \nPreference will be given to applicants within eThekwini Municipality\n \n \nPLEASE NOTE: Transnet, its employees or representatives never ask for a fee from job seekers. Any such requests are fraudulent. Please report any suspicious activities in this regard to the Transnet anti-fraud line on 0800 003 056.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
                "This advert is open for application by external applicants.\n \nEquity Statement : Preference will be given to suitably qualified Applicants who are members of the designated groups in line with the Employment Equity Plan and Targets of the Organisation/Operating Division.\n \nApplicants that are interested in applying for any of the advertised positions must apply by registering on the Careers section of the Transnet Internet. Please take care in completing all required details on the profile, and then apply for the position.\n \nAlternative Application Methods: (Completed Curriculum Vitae to be submitted)\nPost :\nE-mail :\nFax :\n \nThe closing date is on 27.10.2023.\nIt is the responsibility of the applicant to ensure that HR has received the application before the closing date of the advertisement.\nNote: if you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of this advertisement please consider your application as unsuccessful.\nAny questions regarding the application or recruitment process should be sent in writing to ZANELE.SANDI@TRANSNET.NET.\nWe urge all our employees, clients, members of the public and our suppliers to report any kind of fraud or corruption at Transnet. Call the hotline toll free number: 0800 003 056 or email Transnet@tip-offs.com\n \nOperating Division : TPT Saldanha IOT\nPosition Title : Key Accounts Representative\nEmployee Group : Permanent\nDepartment : Customer Serv\nLocation : Saldanha\nReporting To : Senior Specialist: Bus Perf & Monitoring\nGrade Level : F\nReference Number : 203489\n \nPosition Purpose:\nTo ensure that the delivery of the service promise as contained in the Transnet Port Terminals Customer Service Plan is met.\nTo proactively research customer intelligence and providing an analysis and assessment service for information required by Key Accounts Managers.\n \nPosition outputs:\n1. Maximise customer service in the business unit by managing customer service execution interface on a day to day basis.\n2. Custodian for customer service Dashboard/KPI at the business unit.\n3. Facilitate relationship building with all key internal stakeholders (internal capabilities).\n4. Support customer service initiatives.\n5. Account for management of key and ad hoc customers.\n6. Initiative\n \nQualifications & Experience:\n\u2022 Degree / National Diploma in Marketing/ NQF 7 equivalent or other relevant qualification\n\u2022 5 years customer service experience\n\u2022 Valid Drivers\u2019 License\n \nCompetencies:\n\u2022 Experience and knowledge of terminal operations\n\u2022 Extensive knowledge of after sales processes\n\u2022 Problem solving, including analysing and follow-up skills\n\u2022 Ability to pay attention to detail from a service delivery perspective Computer literate (MS Office)\n \nKnowledge required:\n\u2022 Computer literate (MS Office and SAP modules)\n\u2022 Understanding of Commercial contracts\n\u2022 Standard operating procedures for each sector\n\u2022 TPT tariffs\n\u2022 Ability to communicate effectively with all Customers and internal stakeholders Professional and courteous\n \nSkills Required:\n\u2022 Report writing and presentation skills Research skills\n\u2022 Exceptional interpersonal skills, with the ability to command respect from both Customers and colleagues\n \nPLEASE NOTE: Transnet, its employees or representatives never ask for a fee from job seekers. Any such requests are fraudulent. Please report any suspicious activities in this regard to the Transnet anti-fraud line on 0800 003 056.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
