                " \nMMABANA ARTS, CULTURE & SPORTS FOUNDATION\n ",
                " \n \nPART - TIME MANAGER: FACILITIES MAINTENANCE AND DEVELOPMENT\nHead Office\nJob Type: Freelance Contract/Project Based as and when required\nRemuneration Package: Hourly Rate (Based on Gazetted Related Rates)\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nPURPOSE\nTo ensure that Mmabana Arts and Culture and Sport Foundations\u2019 Buildings are well maintained and compliant with legislation and regulations.\nAssist with the development of long term and short term Property Management and Maintenance Policies.\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nImplementation and coordination of projects\nManagement of properties\nStrategic leadership\nStakeholder management\nBusiness Risk Management\nStakeholder management and relationship management\nOverseeing and directing construction projects from conception to completion\nReviewing the project in-depth to schedule deliverables and estimate costs\nOverseeing all onsite and offsite constructions to monitor compliance with building and safety regulations.\nManagement of all aspects of the construction projects and deemed necessary to achieve Project completion and effective operation of the projects;\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nBachelor\u2019s Degree in Civil Engineering (or any qualification in the Built environment)\nProfessional registration in project management with SACPMP \u2013 Pr CPM or and similar bodies is a prerequisite)\nMinimum of 10 years\u2019 experience in executing construction projects management\nPersonal Flexibility and high motivation\nGood communication and excellent reporting skills in English Language\nExcellent Skills in Microsoft office\nExcellent skills in CAD (Computer Aided- Design)\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nADMINISTRATIVE OFFICER - ACADEMY\nHead Office\nJob Type: Permanent Contract\nRemuneration Package: Post Level 7\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nPURPOSE\nTo provide administrative support services to the MACFS Academy\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nMust have knowledge of SETA Learner Management System. Participate in the evaluation of applications and provide input. Capture applications and verify supported appropriate documentation. Generate monthly reports on accredited programmes. Respond to requests from internal and external auditors. Compile relevant statistics for inclusion in appropriate reports when required. Maintain high standards compliance in terms of SETA administration for all regional offices.\nProvide feedback on application status of all academy projects (learnerships, apprenticeships, skills programmes) are registered and enrolled with the relevant SETAs. Coordinate SETA site visits. Good understanding of Quality Management System (QMS).\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nMatric plus Diploma in Administration\nBasic knowledge on Computer Literacy\nOffice Management and Report writing Skills\n2 years working experience in administration\n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \n2 X ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT- ACADEMIC SERVICES\nHead Office\nJob Type: Permanent Contract\nRemuneration Package:\nPost Level 5\nR201 487.59\u202fas a basic salary excluding bonus and benefits\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nPURPOSE\nTo provide administrative support services to the MACFS Academy.\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nMaintain and oversee the filing system of the Academy. Provide support on required LTSM for all regional offices. Provide inventory support and maintain asset register.\n\nCarry out administrative duties such as typing, copying, binding and scanning\nOrganise and schedule meetings and appointments for the Academy. Maintain contact lists and assist in preparation of reports as required. Take minutes of meetings and handle sensitive learner information in a confidential manner.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nMatric.\nBasic knowledge on Computer Literacy\nOffice Management and Report writing Skills\n2 years working experience in administration\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nDIRECTOR: PERFORMING ARTS\nHead Office\nJob Type: Permanent Contract\nRemuneration Package: R 1, 129,551.24 Total Cost to Company Annual Remuneration\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:45\n \nPURPOSE\nThe primary purpose of this position is to curate, administer and manage all music, dance, drama and related performing arts programming in MACSF.\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nDetermining the nature and content of a broad array of performing arts, special-event, and theatre programming for MACSF various performance venues.\nDrafting of strategic plan, standard operating procedures and operational plans for all performing arts units.\nDeveloping and managing the budget for performing arts programming, negotiating and managing contracts with artists and their agents as well as support personnel, including technical and lighting support.\nMaintain an annual maintenance schedule, initiating and supervising maintenance and upgrades of all performance venues, managing production for all events, which includes partnering with stakeholders within the performing arts industry.\nPartnering with the advancement and marketing teams to strategize and plan for sponsorship, advertising, promotion of programming and providing copy for internal publications including MACSF website.\nMust have knowledge of the SCM regulatory framework, PFMA and relevant National Treasury prescripts, LRA, corporate governance and regulations.\nPrepare monthly and quarterly reports for the office of the Chief Executive Officer.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nA relevant Bachelor\u2019s Degree in Dramatic Art, (BA Honours). Master's Degree (MA) will be an added advantage.\nFive (5) year's experience in the field of performing arts at management level.\nValid Driver's License is essential.\n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng. Late submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nREGIONAL DIRECTOR: MMABANA TAUNG\nTaung\nJob Type:\nPermanent Contact\nRemuneration Package:\nR 1, 29,551.24 Total Cost to Company Annual Remuneration\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:37\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nLead, direct and energise an d monitor the entire spectrum of the work of the Foundation in the Region.\nEnsure that in all the units in your centre and/or satellite, the policy of teaching performance and development are pursued with vigour.\nKeep the CEO properly and regularly informed on matters of concern, to exercise financial control and to make recommendations to the CEO as appropriate.\nWork within budget.\nAttend Senior Management meetings regularly and to contribute thereto.\nMaintain close working relations with the Artistic Directors of various art forms as well as other functionaries leading and directing Artistic Sport, Performing Arts and Creative Arts.\nEnsure that the staff at the Certre comply with all policy guidelines and procedures.\nProvide detailed monthly reports on the core business of the Foundation viz the promotion and development of arts, culture and sport.\nMount and conduct an effective outreach programmes.\nDevelop and coordinate staff training programmes.\nExplore, identify and pursue potential avenues for fund raising.\nService and play an active role in functions organised by the Provincial Government as directed by the CEO from time to time including the NW Calabash Festival.\nStrive at all times to maintain healthy working relations with the majority union and to adhere to the spirit of the recognition agreement and acknowledge the existence of the minority unions.\nStrive at all times to maintain healthy working relations with community art associations such as community art centres CAC, Department of Arts, Culture and Sports Recreation.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nAn appropriate recognised three (3) years degree with a minimum of five (5) years management experience.\nExcellent communication and interpersonal skills.\nAbility to develop, control and monitor budget.\nValid drivers' license is essential.\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nSECRETARY TO THE SENIOR MANAGER: H/O CORPORATE SERVICES\nHead Office\nJob Type: To provide secretarial services to the Senior Manager: Corporate Services\nRemuneration Package:\nPost Level 5\nR201 487.08 as a basic salary excluding bonus and benefits\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nPURPOSE\nTo provide secretarial services to the Senior Manager: Corporate Services.\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nProvides Secretarial support services.\nIncoming mail received, recorded manually and filed within 1 day.\nOutgoing mail recorded, filed and dispatched within 1 day.\nManage day to day diary and send reminder to the Senior Manager.\nProvide clerical support services.\nManage meetings.\nArrange accommodation, and Complete S&T claims.\n \nApart from formal interviews, shortlisted candidates may be subjected to practical tests\nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nMatric/ 1-2 years National higher Certificate in Office Administration/Secretarial at NQF level 5 or equivalent qualification\n2\u202f years relevant experience in office administration or secretarial field.\nSecretarial administrative and organisational knowledge and understanding and Computer application knowledge.\nAdministrative and organisational skills, Document management, Oral and written communication skills, Procurement of goods and services, typing, bookkeeping, filling skills and time management.\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nDEPUTY MANAGER: RISK MANAGEMENT\nHead Office\nJob Type: Permanent Contract\nRemuneration Package:\nPost Level 10\nR545 227,44 as a basic salary excluding bonus and benefits\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nPURPOSE\nTo manage fraud and risk office of the Entity.\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nEstablish a risk operations strategy.\nDesign, implementation, maintenance and continuous improvement of operational activities and models.\nImplementation of Group Risk, regulatory and Compliance requirements.\nEnsure the fulfilment of all required governance activities.\nEmployee Benefits, retirement and or group risk administration.\nStakeholder and committee engagement/management.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nBachelor's degree in Risk Management, Compliance or Legal\n8 years' experience in Compliance and Operational Risk\nManagerial experience - minimum of 5 years\nValid Drivers\u2019 License\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nDEPUTY MANAGER: HUMAN RESOURCE ADMINISTRATION AND SUPPORT\nHead Office\nJob Type: Permanent Contract\nRemuneration Package:\nPost Level 10\nR 545 227.44\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nProvides job candidates by screening, interviewing and testing applicants; notifying existing staff of internal opportunities; maintaining personnel records; obtaining temporary staff from agencies.\nMonitors unemployment claims by reviewing claims; substantiating documentation, requesting legal counsel review.\nMaintains human resources records by recording new hires, transfers, terminations, changes in job classifications, merit increases; tracking vacation, sick and personal matters.\nOrients new employees by providing orientation packets; reviewing company policies; gathering withholding and other payroll information; explaining and obtaining signatures for benefit programs.\nDocuments human resources actions by completing, reports, logs and records.\nUpdates job knowledge by participating in educational reading professional publications.\nAccomplishes human resources department and organisation mission by completing related results as needed.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nA National Diploma/ Bachelor's Degree in Human Resource Management, Post -Graduate qualification in Administration will be added advantage.\nA minimum of 5 years\u2019 experience in Human Resource environment of which 3 years must be in HR Administration.\nThe ideal candidate should possess a high level of intergrity, together with well-developed communication skills, computer literacy including Email and Internet will be crucial requirements, self-driven, motivated and proactive person and who is able to work under pressure and to meet deadlines.\nKnowledge of the technical aspects of the VIP System will act as an added advantage.\nValid drivers' license\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.  \nLate submission will not be considered. \n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251 \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nINTERNAL AUDITOR (FINANCIAL AUDITS)\nHead Office\nJob Type:\nRemuneration Package:\nPost Level 7\nR298 699,20 as a basic salary excluding bonus and benefits\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nMust be able to evaluate whether compliance with relevant legislation, National Treasury frameworks and policies has been achieved in the development of the entity's Strategic planning and reporting documents that includes: \nFive years Strategic Plan (SP) with planned projects and programme implementation, Annual Performance Plan (APP) consistent with the medium- term expenditure framework (MTEF) period.\nAnalysis and interpretation of the requirements related to the SP and APP of a public institution. Verification/assessment of the in-year implementation data (evidence) of the QPR against the achievements for the implementation of the APP drawing up of the AR subjected to an annual review and oversight process.\nThe assessment of the reported data related to reliability of performance information reported criteria (Validity, accuracy and completeness).\nEnsure that controls around the development and maintenance and reporting of the SP. APP, QPR and AR are approximately designed and effectively implemented.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nMatric\nBachelor degree in Commerce (Accounting and Auditing) or National Diploma (Internal Auditing)\n1-3\u202fyears working experience in an auditing environment (internal/external audit)\nKnowledge of Internal audit concepts, frameworks and methodologies; frameworks for Performance information, Frameworks for Managing Programme Performance Information, Framework for Strategic Plans and annual Performance and Applicable legislative and regulatory frame work, Public Finance and Management Act (PFMA), Treasury Regulations and\nguidelines; Excel, Word and PowerPoint\nExcellent communication skills the ability to work well with people at all levels are essential\nValid Drivers' license\n \n\nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nPERFORMANCE MONITORING & EVALUATION OFFICER\nHead Office\nJob Type: Permanent Contract\nRemuneration Package:\nPost Level 7\nR298 699,20 as a basic salary excluding bonus and benefits\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nTo compile Organisational monthly, quarterly and annual Reports as per Treasury regulations.\nConduct performance information verification and validations.\nAssist in facilitation and coordination of the Organisational Performance Reviews.\nFacilitate capturing of non-financial data on Provincial Information Management System and QPR system.\nImplementation of the Monitoring & Evaluation framework.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nMatric and three (3) years Diploma/Degree in Administration or equivalent qualification\nCourse in Strategic Management or Monitoring and Evaluation will be an added advantage\nTwo years' experience in the field of Strategic Planning or Monitoring and Evaluation\nComputer literacy. Sound Organisational and interpersonal skills\nAbility to work under pressure\nValid Driver's license\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.  \n \nLate submission will not be considered. \n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251 \n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nSENIOR ACCOUNTANT: MANAGEMENT ACCOUNTING\nHead Office\nJob Type:\nRemuneration Package: R 367 468.44\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:51\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nCompilation of the Annual Budget, Adjustment Budget in line with MTEF of the entity.\nMonitoring the expenditure of the entity against the approved budget.\nCompile In-Year Monitoring reports.\nCompile quarterly financial reports for inclusion in the entity quarterly reports.\nAnalyse financial information to ensure all operations are within the approved budget.\nAssist in shifting of funds where necessary during the adjustment budget process.\nRecording of all grant income from national and provincial departments.\nCompile grants register and reconciliation of grants.\nCompile reconciliations between the entity's bank accounts and the accounting system.\nProvide support in the preparation of Interim and Annual Financial Statements.\nProvide support in during the auditing process by both the Internal and External Auditors.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nA National Diploma or Bachelor's degree in Finance and Auditing\nA minimum of 2 years experience in the accounting/ auditing environment\nCompleted articles with knowledge of ACCPAC will be an added advantage\nA valid driver's license\nThrough knowledge of PFMA Treasury regulations, Regulatory environment and GRAP.\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nASSISTANT KARATE INSTRUCTOR\nMahikeng\nJob Type:\nRemuneration Package:\nR 120.01 (Hourly Rate)\nHours: Four (4) per day\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:51\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nTo train students to develop strength, discipline as well as coordination.\nTo ensure that individuals receive knowledge about different karate moves.\nTo assist in tracking or monitoring student's progress in martial arts and oversee student testing.\nDeveloping relationships with schools.\nPlan and work on your professional development by gaining further teaching or performance competency and continuing your own performance activity.\nEnsuring that you adhere to health and safety standards and insure that work carried out is in line with child protection legislation.\nAdhere and comply with all Institutional policies.\nAdhere and comply to National Karate South African Policies and Procedures\nAdhere and comply to South African Japanese Karate Association Policies and Procedures.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nMinimum of Grade 10-12\nHold the rank of black belt and Karate certifications to gain entry on martial arts clubs.\n2 years experience in conducting, organizing and instructing karate programs.\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport\nFoundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nAEROBICS & ROPE SKIPPING INSTRUCTOR\nLehurutshe\nJob Type:\nRemuneration Package\nRemuneration Package:\nR 120,01 (Hourly Rate)\nHours: Four (4) per day\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:19\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nConduct Aerobics Classes.\nInstruct and supervise participants in Circuit Training and body-building.\nPrepare and participate in Aerobics and Fitness events for Mahikeng/Bojan and the Foundation.\nAssist with general administration of the unit.\nCoach/Instrud Gymnastic Rope Skipping (Render excellent training).\nPrepare learners & participate in Rope skipping events for Mahikeng and MACSF.\nDraw daily attendance register for students.\nAssist with general administration of the unit.\nAssist with preparation of MACSF events\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nCandidates must at least have an Aerobics Instruction Qualification.\nMore than 2 years experience in Aerobics and Fitness/Body-building.\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nAEROBICS & ROPE SKIPPING INS TRUCTOR\nLehurutshe\nJob Type:\nRemuneration Package:\nR 120,01 (Hourly Rate)\nHours: Four (4) per day\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:19\n \nPURPOSE\nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nConduct Aerobics Classes.\nInstruct and supervise participants in Circuit Training and body-building.\nPrepare and participate in Aerobics and Fitness events for Mahikeng/Bojanala and the Foundation.\nAssist with general administration of the unit.\nCoach/Instrud Gymnastic Rope Skipping (Render excellent training).\nPrepare learners & participate in Rope skipping events for Mahikeng and MACSF.\nDraw daily attendance register for students.\nAssist with general administration of the unit.\nAssist with preparation of MACSF events\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nCandidates must at least have an Aerobics Instruction Qualification.\nMore than 2 years\u2019 experience in Aerobics and Fitness/Body-building.\n \n\nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nAEROBICS & ROPE SKIPPING INSTRUCTOR\nBojanala\nJob Type:\nRemuneration Package:\nR 120,01 (Hourly Rate)\nHours: Four (4) per day\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:19\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nConduct Aerobics Classes.\nInstruct and supervise participants in Circuit Training and body-building.\nPrepare and participate in Aerobics and Fitness events for Mahikeng/Bojanala and the Foundation.\nAssist with general administration of the unit.\nCoach/Instrud Gymnastic Rope Skipping (Render excellent training).\nPrepare learners & participate in Rope skipping events for Mahikeng and MACSF.\nDraw daily attendance register for students.\nAssist with general administration of the unit.\nAssist with preparation of MACSF events\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nCandidates must at least have an Aerobics Instruction Qualification.\nMore than 2 years\u2019 experience in Aerobics and Fitness/Body-building.\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nMUSIC TUTOR\nMahikeng\nJob Type:\nRemuneration Package:\nR 182,27 (Hourly Rate)\nHours: Four (4) per day\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:56\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nTeaching practical piano, individual students, develop and create.\nPrepare students for examinations (practical).\nPerforming during Mmabana events and students functions.\nTechnical assistance to the music and other departments-sound choreography worksh ops i.e. Calabash.\nEnsure assets control.\nEnsure vibrancy and viability in the unit by maintaining high students numbers.\nPerform/carry out reasonable duties when requested to do so.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nGrade 12 plus Relevent Tertiary Qualification at NQF Level 7.\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nDRAMA TUTOR\nTaung\nJob Type:\nRemuneration Package:\nR 182.27 (Hourly Rate)\nHours: Four (4) per day\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:02\n \nPURPOSE\nTo be responsible for all duties as required of an academic educator.\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nHave knowledge of programme facilitation and assessment principles.\nShow understanding and expertise for unit standards and/or skills programmes registered with CATHSSETA.\nMust have knowledge and perform visual art functions in the field/subject of expertise and be familiar with the work across the sector.\nAnalyse, describe, evaluate works of art created by learners Understand and describe the arts in their historical, social, and cultural contexts.\nEnsure that adequate learning materials are available for teaching and learning.\nComply with MACSF policies and procedures on SETA accredited programmes.\nUnderstand the SAQA and NQF Act 67 of 2008 Level description.\nAdhere to MACSF academic work schedule on training and development.\nPrepare monthly and quarterly reports for the office of the Director Performing Arts.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nBachelor of Arts in Dramatic Arts.\nAssessor and Moderator competency will be added advantage.\n2-5 years working experience within the field\n \n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251\n \n \n \n ",
                " \n \n \n \nMEDIA LIAISON OFFICER\nJob Type: Permanent Contract\nRemuneration Package:\nPost Level 6\nR 241 944.96\nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nDraft media statements/brief articles.\nMedia liaison including developing relationships with core media list.\nCollect, maintain and archive news stories about Mmabana.\nCollect, prepare content or documents for website update.\nMonitor and update social media outlets with relevant news and information.\nDevelop and maintain stakeholder database.\nSpecial event support.\nGeneral office administration.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nAn appropriate recognised three year qualification in Communication, Journalism, Public relations.\nA minimum of five (5) years\u2019 experience in the relevant fields.\nThe successful candidate must also be computer literate (packages such as Microsoft, Excel, Power-point, MS Word, E-mail, Internet).\nStrong interpersonal, oral and written communication skills.\nValid driver's license\n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; OR Hand- post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @072 687 7251",
                "DEPUTY MANAGER: LEGAL SERVICES\nHead Office\nJob Type: PERMANENT CONTRACT\nRemuneration Package:\nPOST LEVEL 10\nR545 227.44 (ANNUAL BASIC SALARY)\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nPURPOSE\nThe Deputy Manager: Legal Services shall provide legal services and support including Labour relations matters, vetting of policies, charters and related legal documents. Ensure that the administrative and contractual decisions of MACSF are compliant with governing legislation and conduct awareness sessions on the impact of any new legislative requirements and related issues.\n \nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nGood understanding of legislations applicable to Public Service, policy formulation, contract drafting and management.\nManage the resolution of legal disputes which includes representing MACSF at arbitrations, in a court of law and liaising with appointed legal professions.\nTo provide the Directors of the Board with guidance to their duties, responsibilities, powers, good governance and changes in the legislation.\nTo ensure that minutes of the Board meetings of any other committee are properly recorded.\nPrepare monthly and quarterly reports for the office of the Executive Management meetings.\nMaintain up-to-date logs of papers discussed at committees and decisions made.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nA relevant Bachelor\u2019s Degree in Law, (LLB/LLM).\n3-5 years\u2019 experience in interpreting and advising on relevant legislations.\nMembership of the Law Society of South Africa (ISSA) or relevant bodies will be added advantage.\nA Valid driver\u2019s license is essential.\n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251",
                "DEPUTY MANAGER - REVENUE AND BUDGET\nHead Office\nJob Type: Permanent Contract\nRemuneration Package:\nPOST LEVEL 10\nR545 227,44 as a basic salary, excluding bonus and benefits\n \nClosing Date: 9 November 2023 at 16:30:00\n \nPURPOSE\nDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\nOversee revenue management across the entity's offices\nManaging and coordinating monthly reporting, budgeting and reforecast processes\nEnsuring that revenue transactions are accurately recorded,\nEnsuring that the entity collects all revenue due to it\nEnsuring that all regional offices perform monthly reconciliations Monitoring cash flow.\nProviding insights on the financial health of the entity.\nEnsuring the entity meets all its statutory and compliance obligations. Looking for cost-reduction opportunities.\nPreparing the annual budget for the entity\nPreparing monthly financial statements, Interim Financial Statement and Annual Financial Statements and supporting working papers in line with Grap. Develop, monitor and review entity accounting policies, procedures and processes.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nA National Diploma or Bachelor's degree in Accounting and/ Auditing.\nA minimum of five (5) years work experience in an accounting environment, of which two (2) years must be at supervisory level.\nThorough knowledge of PFMA, GRAP, Treasury regulations and the\nregulatory environment.\nKnowledge of ACCPAC and Caseware\nCompleted articles will be an added advantage.\nA valid driving licence\n \nHow to apply\nSenior Manager: Corporate Services, Mmabana Arts, Culture and Sport Foundation, Private bag X33, Mmabatho, 2735 or marked attention: Mr. Collins Gopane, Mmabana Mahikeng Region; Or Hand-post applications can be delivered to the following address: Physical Address: 101 Dr James Moroka Drive; Mmabana Mahikeng.\n \nLate submission will not be considered.\n \nEnquiries\nEnquiries should be forwarded to Mr. Collins Gopane @ 072 687 7251"
